    <article id="main-content" class="article">
      <header class="article-header">
        <h1 title="How to Create and Use a Fleet in C4 PTR" class="article-title">
          How to Create and Use a Fleet in C4 PTR
          
        </h1>

        <div class="article-author">
          
          <div class="article-meta">
            

            <div class="meta-group">
              
                <span class="meta-data"><time datetime="2026-06-04T13:09:09Z" title="2026-06-04T13:09:09Z" data-datetime="relative">June 04, 2026 13:09</time></span>
                <span class="meta-data">Updated</span>
              
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        
          <div class="article-subscribe"><div data-helper="subscribe" data-json="{&quot;item&quot;:&quot;article&quot;,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;/hc/en-us/articles/52251721868563-How-to-Create-and-Use-a-Fleet-in-C4-PTR/subscription.json&quot;,&quot;follow_label&quot;:&quot;Follow&quot;,&quot;unfollow_label&quot;:&quot;Unfollow&quot;,&quot;following_label&quot;:&quot;Following&quot;,&quot;can_subscribe&quot;:true,&quot;is_subscribed&quot;:false}"></div></div>
        
      </header>

      <section class="article-info">
        <div class="article-content">
          <div class="article-body"><p>After importing your ships and resources into C4 PTR, you can create a fleet from your faction CSS and use it for actions such as movement, mining, scanning, and other fleet operations.</p><p>This guide explains how to create a fleet, add ships and resources, undock it, and access its available actions.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XQKKRY0YXQFB1JB72QPKW">Before you start</h2><p>Before creating a fleet, make sure you have imported your ships and resources into C4 PTR.</p><p>If you have not done this yet, check the <a href="/hc/en-us/articles/52243005225363"><strong>How to Get Started in C4 PTR</strong></a> and <a href="/hc/en-us/articles/52243667123603"><strong>How to Import Assets in C4 PTR</strong></a> guides first.</p><p>Once your assets are imported, go to your faction CSS and enter the Starbase.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 2406/1953;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52251706684563" width="2406" height="1953"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XQYJBQN5M7GKM5VSE8W6Y">Step 1: Open the Hangar</h2><p>From the Starbase menu:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e299649c9a2424d17923d6d7254514bfb">
<p>Click <strong>Hangar</strong>.</p>
<figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 2409/1132;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52251706687251" width="2409" height="1132"></figure>
</li>
<li data-list-item-id="edd4efcdcc3245b00e856b3d1862ad623">
<p>Click <strong>Form Fleet</strong> or <strong>Create a New Fleet</strong>.</p>
<figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 2394/854;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52251721859859" width="2394" height="854"></figure>
</li>
</ol><p>This will open the fleet creation screen.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XR2KMQKFN0E8JE0DTZF2K">Step 2: Add ships to your fleet</h2><p>In the fleet creation screen, you can choose which ships you want to add to your new fleet.</p><p>To add ships:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e92f410b4a6668e1a5bfcf1007c84d87b">Find the ship you want to add from the list on the right.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ea26c46db322dad4b14c877ae3c6b9611">Enter the quantity you want to add, or click <strong>MAX</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eede3ca70fd972b9ce46c3965d520bf9c">
<p>Click <strong>Add to Fleet</strong>.</p>
<figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 850/625;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52251721860499" width="850" height="625"></figure>
</li>
</ol><p>The selected ships will be added to the fleet staging area.</p><p>You can repeat this process if you want to add more ships to the same fleet.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XR6VDRY5XN3Z0H2FHA4CN">Step 3: Add resources and supplies</h2><p>After adding ships, you can add resources and supplies to your fleet.</p><p>Your fleet may require different resources depending on the actions you want to perform:</p><figure class="wysiwyg-table wysiwyg-table-align-left"><table>
<thead><tr>
<th>Supply</th>
<th>Used for</th>
</tr></thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Fuel Pod Fuel</strong></td>
<td>Required for fleet movement, such as Warp and Subwarp</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Ammo Pod Ammunition</strong></td>
<td>Required for combat and for mining with most ships</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Food</strong></td>
<td>Required to mine raw resources</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Repair Kits</strong></td>
<td>Required for scanning, fleet repairs, and Starbase repairs</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table></figure><blockquote><p><strong>Note:</strong> Armstrong miners do not require ammo for mining.</p></blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><p>To add resources or supplies:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e88839dbc3f8cb857974fbb1d122c8064">Click one of the fleet storage areas, such as <strong>Support Modules</strong> or <strong>Support Cargo Hold</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e6d8e5df0903d56a2b190bd3e73032418">The list on the right will update and show available resources instead of ships.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e289a14b7865b6d818efd80ae593573f8">Find the resource you want to add.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e562f628063a2b0fede74caaf3ef65ecd">Enter a quantity or click <strong>MAX</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e94bfafee4726198ae371c05faa0e17b7">Click <strong>Add to Fleet</strong>.</li>
</ol><p>Be careful when selecting fuel or ammunition. Some resources have different versions depending on where they are stored.</p><p>For example:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="ea519ed03f7d0d6c12f3606965f7314f7">
<strong>Fuel - Fuel Pod</strong> is used for fleet movement.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e9ff8a8848e2babcfad9cd06fd9e86e79">
<strong>Fuel -&nbsp;Cargo Hold</strong> is stored as cargo and is not used the same way for flight.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e2b6ded093b3e4a7fc678f976cba87fa4">
<strong>Ammunition -&nbsp;Ammo Pod</strong> is used for combat and mining with most ships.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eb9f56be82b2c55e22cbc2cd05454ce8d">
<strong>Ammunition -&nbsp;Cargo Hold</strong> is stored as cargo and is not used the same way for combat or mining.</li>
</ul><p>Make sure you add the correct version for the action you want your fleet to perform.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 2399/874;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52251706690323" width="2399" height="874"></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XRBA6QJBYC66MPP18H8JR">Important: choose the correct fuel and ammunition type</h2><p>Some resources may have different versions depending on where they are stored or how they are used.</p><p>For example:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="e8f58a1c9fd66fe1555b84cc2fde97ae4">
<strong>Ammunition - Ammo Pod</strong> can be used for combat.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e523c38c0ea5bb639553da61c67cbd54d">
<strong>Ammunition - Cargo Hold</strong> is stored in the cargo hold and cannot be used for combat.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e2329f1957e84b3595cd798cb86a9e852">
<strong>Fuel - Fuel Pod</strong> is used as fleet fuel.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e8de1cc3c66c40a77fa69208b3e96dd67">
<strong>Fuel - Cargo Hold</strong> is stored in the cargo hold and is not used the same way as Fuel Pod fuel.</li>
</ul><p>Be careful when adding fuel or ammunition to your fleet. If you place the wrong type in the wrong storage area, it may not be usable for the action you want to perform.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 788/607;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52251706691347" width="788" height="607"></figure><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XRHDKW3YP3DPMK70P8N5T">Step 4: Form the fleet</h2><p>Once you have selected the ships and resources you want to add:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e1c5264a6a3cfcc72480b961c5fb41500">Review the fleet staging area.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e9fdbf7c1d5a367b9b26c0c8b2ad23468">Make sure your ships, supplies, crew, and resources are correct.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e2368cdcc4c7b0bcce8eab02f4877f1d0">
<p>Click <strong>Form Fleet</strong>.</p>
<p><img src="/hc/article_attachments/52251721863187" width="536" height="259"></p>
</li>
</ol><p>Your fleet will now be created.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XRNZGTTN0VWRQJQ6SXBSB">Step 5: Undock your fleet</h2><p>After the fleet is created, it will appear in the Hangar view.</p><p>To start using it:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="ec3195441a0bddb469c6638df9c2da563">Select the fleet from the Hangar.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e5aa96f02fe8401f5dacc8dd568958e8d">
<p>Click <strong>Undock</strong>.</p>
<p><img src="/hc/article_attachments/52251706692627" width="2391" height="1757"></p>
</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ec1e52dec70787c3f2d8df04da7de4e9a">Wait for the fleet to undock.</li>
</ol><p>Once the fleet is undocked, you can close the Starbase and Hangar menus.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XRT8ET83GPHXAD19K92TQ">Step 6: Access your fleet from the map</h2><p>You can access your fleet from the main map.</p><p>To find it:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="e6f941826c4bf993e7fa9d1f9bfd5e720">
<p>Open the <strong>My Fleets</strong> menu from the top menu bar.</p>
<p><img src="/hc/article_attachments/52251721864339" width="1000" height="718"></p>
</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e5ef9a615c96a54f3aab29929dd5c4ed3">Select the fleet you want to use.</li>
</ol><p>This will open the fleet view on the left side of the screen.</p><figure class="wysiwyg-image"><img style="aspect-ratio: 652/1086;" src="/hc/article_attachments/52251721864979" width="652" height="1086"></figure><p>From this view, you can see the fleet’s status, supplies, cargo, and available actions.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XRYMK6J8KRQ6DJXVAQ3GE">Step 7: Use fleet actions</h2><p>Once your fleet is selected, you can use the available fleet actions.</p><p>Depending on the fleet and its current state, available actions may include:</p><ul>
<li data-list-item-id="edc034409d582743b45a11bcb34192dae">Dock</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e113f37e743c50edbe88d52cd5ab36ad7">Warp</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eae3c00b39c7a07475509c75ab1a21f41">Subwarp</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e14aaa60281d9f6d740833eade3d7c69c">Warp Gate</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ec33bb5850c12f6e5da0e3061ee9074fc">Repair Base</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e51a82f5c6a394ea5ba32ef63a2361f38">Repair Fleet</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e957801d99a8718eed436716181bc30aa">Destruct</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ea4711481150cde1378c797fae2a670d9">Mine</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e335a243e0cd60c5723b764785890fb3b">Scan</li>
</ul><p>&nbsp;</p><hr><p>&nbsp;</p><h2 id="h_01KT4XS2PA1P0EADEAC2FY7QKY">Summary</h2><p>To create a fleet in C4 PTR:</p><ol>
<li data-list-item-id="eec4273e5ea0b96b2f1b7240ccc2ffb07">Import your ships and resources.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ea5d9fe763912db68456014d8e517048f">Go to your faction CSS.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ea1bb93240ccc6caf058be7d599cf8618">Enter the Starbase.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="ee901521fc16f74df2890c8b127c46628">Open <strong>Hangar</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e8192ae985f9502fdc1c19c497e92fe46">Click <strong>Form Fleet</strong> or <strong>Create a New Fleet</strong>.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e8d979dddae39e416c266db0d09e0d82a">Add ships to the fleet.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="eafa270654b8e8e03f5f238ff0363098e">Add the resources or supplies you need.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e3f2efab186517a65b092629fbb062550">Make sure fuel and ammunition are added in the correct form.</li>
<li data-list-item-id="e24c205dca4b5f208708c9483ca772feb">Click <strong>Form Fleet</strong>.</li>
</ol></div>

          

          
        </div>
      </section>

